edu.vserver.exercises.model
Interface EditorMaterialManager

All Superinterfaces:
ExerciseMaterialManager, java.io.Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
StubEditorMaterialManagerImpl
public interface EditorMaterialManager
extends ExerciseMaterialManager

This interface represents an abstract interface through which the Editor implementors delete, add and save file-materials that can be used in the exercises.

Implementors of this class handle the specifics of saving the files somewhere persistently and associating the materials with certain ExerciseData -instance defining a concrete exercise so that when the given exercise is loaded all the materials saved to it are also loaded.

If given Editor wants to use EditorMaterialManager it must first be initialized by calling initialize() giving the implementor change to create some temporary storage system. If materials are not explicitly saved via calling saveNewMaterial(ExerciseMaterial) they are deleted when the editor is exited.

EditorMaterialManager extends ExerciseMaterialManager making it possible to pass the EditorMaterialManager object directly to the Executor when giving an option to test exercise under edit directly from the Editor.

Author:
Riku Haavisto, Johannes Holvitie

Method Detail

initialize

void initialize()
Must be called if used before calling any other methods. Initializes all the needed system resources.

addMaterial

ExerciseMaterial addMaterial(java.io.InputStream tempFileStream,
                             java.lang.String fileTypeExt)
Adds a new ExerciseMaterial to the temporary storage managed by the EditorMaterialManager. The new material will only be truly saved persistently with call to saveNewMaterial(ExerciseMaterial). It will be visible though to for example possible testing view even before it is persistently saved.

Parameters:
tempFileStream - stream of the file to be saved
fileTypeExt - extension of the file to be saved; can also be "", in some cases setting the correct extension (eg. jpg) is needed for correctly showing the file in a browser
Returns:
ExerciseMaterial representing the newly added material

deleteMaterial

void deleteMaterial(ExerciseMaterial material)
Deletes the given material from the temporary storage and also from the persistent storage if the given ExerciseMaterial is already stored persistently.

Parameters:
material - ExerciseMaterial to delete

saveNewMaterial

ExerciseMaterial saveNewMaterial(ExerciseMaterial material)
Stores a given ExerciseMaterial persistently and returns a new ExerciseMaterial-object that will have an identifier through which it can be fetched from the persistent storage ( #getMaterial(int)). These ids are valid for storing to the ExerciseData-objects if for example certain image file must be associated with certain correct answer (etc).

Parameters:
material - ExerciseMaterial to save
Returns:
a new ExerciseMaterial object that will have a globally valid and persistent (until explicit deletion) id
